STEF: <i>You locked me in
a room with some man</i>

00:14.943 --> 00:17.978
who preceded to tell me
that being gay was a sin.

00:18.013 --> 00:19.245
Well, I was being a parent,

00:19.280 --> 00:21.280
I was pushing you in
the right direction.

00:21.315 --> 00:23.583
Hey, Dad! Dad?

00:23.618 --> 00:24.884
Is Stef here?

00:24.919 --> 00:26.252
You're not talking to my wife.

00:26.287 --> 00:27.754
You have feelings for her?

00:27.789 --> 00:31.391
No, I have feelings about her.

00:31.426 --> 00:32.625
Alter some of your cells,

00:32.659 --> 00:34.827
then reinsert them into your
body to attack the cancer.

00:34.863 --> 00:36.038
- BRANDON: How you doin'?
- Good.

00:36.062 --> 00:37.062
It seems like it.

00:37.097 --> 00:38.764
BRANDON: <i>I have something for you.</i>

00:38.799 --> 00:42.100
JUDGE: <i>It's clear Mr. and Mrs.
Sinfuego are honorable people.</i>

00:42.105 --> 00:44.655
I order that they be
released from detention,

00:44.660 --> 00:47.539
after which they are to report
to Immigration and Customs

00:47.574 --> 00:49.574
for immediate deportation.

00:49.610 --> 00:50.975
CALLIE: <i>No, I didn't get in.</i>

00:51.011 --> 00:52.943
Maybe art isn't your true calling.

00:52.978 --> 00:55.780
I was impressed with how much
you knew about that case law.

00:55.815 --> 00:58.081
I want to change my major to law.

01:00.453 --> 01:04.120
